summary: Let’s Talk About Pokemon - The Sandile Family
title: Let’s Talk About Pokemon - The Sandile Family
body:
551: Sandile

And like I said, almost immediately after Basculin, Gen 5 goes whole-ham with its creativity. Almost as if these two were to go with Hippopotas from Gen 4, they introduce yet another “the sand is water” Pokemon in Sandile! An adorable baby crocodile that dwells in the desert thanks to the film of translucent scales covering its eyes. Which are not only goggles, but are totally meant to be sunglasses! Which makes this line all the more fun later on.

Personal Score: 8/10

Sandile wants to be one of the cool kids.

552: Krokorok

Krokorok is a bit of what you’d expect Sandile to evolve into. And a bit what you’d expect out of an anthropomorphic crocodile without much variation. So much so to the point where it wouldn’t look too out of place in Donkey Kong Country. But it does get a smug look on its face, and the “sunglasses” are definitely looking even more like sunglasses now. Combine that with this line’s Dark typing, and the fact that its cry sounds like a rockin electric guitar, and you’ll probably see where they’re going with this.

Personal Score: 8/10

Cool!

553: Krookodile

Krookodile could’ve very easily been nothing more than a bigger Krokorok. BUT. It takes on a totally new colorscheme, now sporting a hella black and red. Its cry sounds even more rockin. And just look at those sunglasses.

There is no way this Pokemon isn’t going for the anime bully/delinquent/criminal look with those pointy shades. It’s even got an obnoxious “trench coat” look going on, with the black pointed stripes now looking a bit more like the belt straps. And that name is just absolutely perfect. What a boss. What a crime boss. It’s just hilarious that they turned what could’ve been a simple “aquatic animal that lives in the desert instead” has actually turned into that. But at the same time it’s a huge asshole gang boss that forms a gang of its fellow Krokoroks and Sandiles.

Personal Score: 9.5/10

The baddest croc on the block

Overall:

I know I already said back in Roggenrola’s review that that was when Gen 5 picked up. But this is when Gen 5 goes even further beyond.

[Archive]

title: Pokemon Masterlist
body:
after realizing how much amazing pokemon replacements there are for Stardew Valley, I decided to make a masterlist!

Crops

  • Pokecrops

Etc

  • Pokemon dolls
  • Pokemon elements (town edits, character edits, etc)
  • Pokefish

Livestock

  • Pokemon retextures
  • Machoke (cow)
  • Machop (calf)
  • Slowbro as pig, Flaaffy as sheep
  • Farm pokemon
  • Mareep (sheep)

Pets

  • Umbreon (cat)
  • Eevee (cat)
  • Skitty (cat)
  • Furret (dog)
  • Mimikyu (both)
  • Mew (cat)
  • Leafeon (cat)
  • Vulpix (cat)
  • Litten (cat)
  • Goomy (both)
  • Togepi (dog)
  • Glaceon (cat)
  • Espeon (cat)
  • Sylveon (both)
  • Dratini (both)
  • Alolan Vulpix (cat)
  • Starter pokemon
  • Shaymin
  • Meowth (cat)
  • Shinx (cat)
  • Growlithe (dog)
  • Several dog pokemon (dog)

Horses
Ponyta
Altaria
Entei, Raikou and Suicune
Latias and Latios

As far as clothes go, I’m p sure Get Dressed comes with pokemon outfits, and the post with the Growlithe dog has hats

There are more replacements out there, these are just the ones I liked/noticed first!

Latias and Latios

As far as clothes go, I’m p sure Get Dressed comes with pokemon outfits, and the post with the Growlithe dog has hats

There are more replacements out there, these are just the ones I liked/noticed first!
trail.content:
after realizing how much amazing pokemon replacements there are for Stardew Valley, I decided to make a masterlist!

Crops

  • Pokecrops

Etc

  • Pokemon dolls
  • Pokemon elements (town edits, character edits, etc)
  • Pokefish

Livestock

  • Pokemon retextures
  • Machoke (cow)
  • Machop (calf)
  • Slowbro as pig, Flaaffy as sheep
  • Farm pokemon
  • Mareep (sheep)

Pets

  • Umbreon (cat)
  • Eevee (cat)
  • Skitty (cat)
  • Furret (dog)
  • Mimikyu (both)
  • Mew (cat)
  • Leafeon (cat)
  • Vulpix (cat)
  • Litten (cat)
  • Goomy (both)
  • Togepi (dog)
  • Glaceon (cat)
  • Espeon (cat)
  • Sylveon (both)
  • Dratini (both)
  • Alolan Vulpix (cat)
  • Starter pokemon
  • Shaymin
  • Meowth (cat)
  • Shinx (cat)
  • Growlithe (dog)
  • Several dog pokemon (dog)

Horses
Ponyta
Altaria
Entei, Raikou and Suicune
Latias and Latios

As far as clothes go, I’m p sure Get Dressed comes with pokemon outfits, and the post with the Growlithe dog has hats

There are more replacements out there, these are just the ones I liked/noticed first!
